WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.000
Borealis is a Canadian research data repository supported by academic libraries, research institutions, and the digital research alliance of Canada.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:16.000
It offers a user-friendly and collaborative environment for sharing datasets and includes several key features.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:23.000
Built-on Dataverse Open Source Software, hosted by Scholars Portal and the University of Toronto Libraries.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Single-sign-on-access for Canadian researchers integrated through the Canadian Access Federation.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:37.000
Indexed for discovery in major services like data site, Google dataset search, and Lunaris, making your data easier to find in-site.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Borealis is particularly well-suited for institutions looking for decentralized management of research data, supported by librarians and local administrators.

